data.name: priceconcept_infobox_body
data.value: We want you feel safe that your price with elKompis are cheaper than most. No fuzz. Guaranteed no small writing. That is why you can see and your price and control how your price is compared to the market. Maybe not the cheapest. But guaranteed cheap. No bullshit, no cheating. data.name: greenconcept_infobox_header
data.value: Your CO2 savings with 100 % renewable energy

data.name: greenconcept_info
data.value: elKompis provides you with only 100 % renewable energy which reduces your carbon footprint significantly and saves the environment. Our goal is to accelerate demand for sustainable solutions. We want both you and us to take responsible choices. Your most sustainable energy, is the energy you don't use. By reducing your consumption, you will make the best choice for the planet. But the second best, is renewable energy, guaranteed by energy certificates of origin. This guarantees that your consumption comes from renewable energy sources. The environmental effect can be explained through trees. We calculate your power consumption in the spruce trees' binding of carbon. One spruce tree binds 2000 kg CO2 in its 50 year lifespan. Every year of the tree's life, it binds 40 kg, which is 3,3 kg a month. Non-renewable kWh equals 0,509 kg CO2. We hope this calculation will engage you and motivate you, to keep on making the best choices. Together we can make a difference. <3

data.name: consumption_advice_tip_one_body
data.value: Bruk appen og planlegg strømbruken ut fra når strømprisen er lavest. Du kan spare masse på å redusere strømforbruket i de dyreste timene. Det anbefales ikke å bruke brannfarlige produkter om natten.

data.name: consumption_advice_tip_two_heading
data.value: Senk temperaturen inne med én grad.

data.name: consumption_advice_tip_two_body
data.value: In the average Norwegian household, heating makes for about 60-80 % of the total energy usage. By turning the indoor temperature down by just 1 degree you can reduce your energy usage by as much as 5 %. A general recommendation is to keep the indoor temperature at 18-21 °C. for a comfortable yet energy efficient living.

data.name: consumption_advice_tip_three_body
data.value: The energy cost is usually lower during night-time. If you have a safe and smart home electrical vehicle charging station, you might want to consider charging your car overnight. Remember that with the smart charging from elKompis, your car will be automatically charged during the time when the price on energy is the lowest.

data.name: consumption_advice_tip_four_body
data.value: When your computer and TV is not in use, it is recommended to turn them off completely rather than having them on standby mode. Many electronics use the same amount of energy when they are in standby as when they are being used. Therefore, you should make it a habit to turn your electronics off then they are not in use.

data.name: consumption_advice_tip_five_body
data.value: Second to heating a household, warm water supply makes up for the most energy usage in Norwegian households. About 20 % of your energy usage is for powering your warm water supply. In times when energy prices are high, it might be smart to have quicker showers than usual.
